google_play_reviews.replyContent: Passive Jammer only uses MediaRecorder and AudioRecord functions to access microphone hardware as a way of blocking other user apps from accessing the microphone as per Android API, it does not access audio data in any way. There is no interaction with audio/sound out other than via the Active Jammer which will mostly make audible sounds.

google_play_reviews.replyContent: PilferShush Jammer uses a microphone with a diagonal slash symbol for both the passive service and for the active service notification. So you will see two notification symbols if both services are running. Passive/Active service found just indicates that the main app UI has recognised its own services as either running or not running.

google_play_reviews.replyContent: Audio output generated by this app is via the device speaker ~60dBA. An audio signal frequency between 20Hz and 24kHz itself will not harm any living thing with ears. However, the amplitude of a given audio signal can do harm. But in the case of this app it would require more amplitude than any mobile device can generate, ie + 100dBA.
